      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do you hit protein goals when eating out socially?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">The most effective strategy is pre-loading — eating a high-protein snack (Greek yogurt, cottage cheese, or a hard-boiled egg) 30–60 minutes before a social meal. This adds 15–20g before you sit down and blunts appetite so you make calmer, more strategic choices at the table. At the meal, anchor your plate around whatever protein entrée is available.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What do you eat at a pizza night to get enough protein?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Two to three slices of meat-topped pizza provides roughly 20–25g of protein. The move is to pre-load 20g before you arrive, eat the pizza normally, and prioritize wings if available (6 wings = 24g). One lower-protein social meal doesn't derail a week if your other meals are consistently on target.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do you get protein at a client dinner without being difficult?</div>
