        <div class="faq-a">Pre-loading means eating a small, high-protein snack 30–60 minutes before a social meal where you expect limited protein options. Greek yogurt (17g), cottage cheese (14g), two hard-boiled eggs (12g), or a protein shake (20–25g) all work. It adds protein before the meal starts and blunts appetite so you make calmer choices at the table.</div>
